Looking at the error, Block 2 `hex (8 11 10 9 12 15 14 13)` has inward-pointing faces because all vertices 8-15 share x=25, making the block degenerate. I need to redesign the entire mesh geometry based on the official OpenFOAM squareBend tutorial structure.

The key issue is that the bend vertices don't connect properly between blocks. I need to create a proper stepped geometry where:
- Block 0: Inlet straight duct (x: -50 to 0)
- Block 1: Bend elbow connecting inlet to post-bend duct
- Block 2: Post-bend straight duct
- Block 3: Extended outlet duct

I'll reposition vertices so all blocks span valid 3D volumes with proper right-hand rule ordering.

