1. Properly shared vertices between blocks (no duplication)
2. Block 1 now has two valid hexes forming the bend
3. Block 2 connects the bend to the post-bend duct and continues to outlet
4. Block 3 is the long outlet duct
5. All hexes follow right-hand rule with outward-pointing faces

